<?xml version=”1.0” encoding=”UTF-8” standalone=”yes”?><rsdl><description>A cosine, sine, and tangent calculator for sides of a right triangle. Each of the three operations will accept, as input, integer or floating point values representing the non-hypotenuse legs of a right triangle. For every operation, there’s a parameter opp, representing the leg opposite the angle to measure, and adj representing the leg adjacent to the angle to measure. The API services offered by this app are named cosine, sine, and tangent, and will be accessible at /api/cosine, /api/sine, and /api/tangent. Each of them takes the above values as GET parameters only, and will yield a JSON-formatted dictionary result containing exactly two decimal fields: result and hyp. These fields contain, respectively, the result of the requested calculation, and the computed hypotenuse length of the right triangle.</description><version major=”1” minor=”0” build=”0” revision=”12” /><links><link rel=”get” href=”/api/sine”><request><url><parameters_set><parameter type=”xs:decimal” required=”true”><name>opp</name><value>Length of leg opposite angle being measured</value></parameter><parameter type=”xs:decimal” required=”true”><name>adj</name><value>Length of leg adjacent to angle being measured</value></parameter></parameters_set></url></request><response><type>JSON containing result &amp; hypotenuse calculations</type></response></link><link rel=”get” href=”/api/cosine”><request><url><parameters_set><parameter type=”xs:decimal” required=”true”><name>opp</name><value>Length of leg opposite angle being measured</value></parameter><parameter type=”xs:decimal” required=”true”><name>adj</name><value>Length of leg adjacent to angle being measured</value></parameter></parameters_set></url></request><response><type>JSON containing result &amp; hypotenuse calculations</type></response></link><link rel=”get” href=”/api/tangent”><request><url><parameters_set><parameter type=”xs:decimal” required=”true”><name>opp</nam